{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"This construct enables a serializable representation of a DOM Range.","type":"text"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/JSONEquatable","doc:\/\/Readium\/s28CustomDebugStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/Readium\/SQ"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DOMRange"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In a DOM Range object, the startContainer + startOffset tuple represents the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"start"},{"type":"text","text":" boundary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"point. Similarly, the the endContainer + endOffset tuple represents the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"end"},{"type":"text","text":" boundary point."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In both cases, the start\/endContainer property is a pointer to either a DOM text node, or a DOM"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"element (this typically depends on the mechanism from which the DOM Range instance originates,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example when obtaining the currently-selected document fragment using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"window.selection"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API). In the case of a DOM text node, the start\/endOffset corresponds to a position within the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"character data. In the case of a DOM element node, the start\/endOffset corresponds to a position"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that designates a child text node."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"end"},{"text":" field is optional. When only the start field is specified, the domRange object","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"represents a “collapsed” range that has identical ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"start"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"end"},{"text":" boundary points.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"https:\/\/github.com\/readium\/architecture\/blob\/master\/models\/locators\/extensions\/html.md#the-domrange-object","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Structures","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange\/Point"],"generated":true,"title":"Structures"},{"anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange\/init(json:warnings:)","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange\/init(start:end:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Initializers"},{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange\/json"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties"},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange\/CustomDebugStringConvertible-Implementations","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange\/Equatable-Implementations"],"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/readiumshared\/domrange"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/ReadiumShared\/DOMRange","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"DOMRange","roleHeading":"Structure","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DOMRange","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"s